# GKE Module

This Terraform module creates Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) clusters, node pools, and related resources for both development and production environments.

## Features

- ✅ **GKE Clusters** - Create clusters with configurable settings
- ✅ **Node Pools** - Create multiple node pools with different configurations
- ✅ **Private Clusters** - Secure clusters with private nodes and endpoints
- ✅ **Workload Identity** - Secure access to Google Cloud services
- ✅ **Binary Authorization** - Enforce deployment policies
- ✅ **Network Policy** - Control traffic flow between pods
- ✅ **Autoscaling** - Cluster and node pool autoscaling
- ✅ **Monitoring & Alerting** - Comprehensive monitoring
- ✅ **Service Accounts** - Dedicated service accounts
- ✅ **IAM Integration** - Fine-grained access control
- ✅ **Security Features** - Shielded nodes, secure boot, integrity monitoring
- ✅ **Cost Optimization** - Preemptible nodes, autoscaling, resource management

## Usage

### Call from another repository

Point `source` at this repo and the path under it (`//Gcp/GKE`). Pin **`ref` to a tag or commit** in production, not a branch that can change.

```hcl
module "gke" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Gcp/GKE?ref=main"
  # Use ?ref=v1.0.0 (or a commit SHA) once you tag releases
  # ...same inputs as in Basic Usage below
}
```

The **root** module where you call this must configure the **Google** provider (project, region, and auth). This module only declares it needs `hashicorp/google` and `hashicorp/time` — it does not set credentials:

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    google = {
      source  = "hashicorp/google"
      version = ">= 5.0.0"
    }
    time = {
      source  = "hashicorp/time"
      version = ">= 0.9.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "google" {
  project = var.project_id
  region  = var.region
}
```

`provider "time"` is optional; the default `time` provider is enough for this module.

### Basic Usage

```hcl
module "gke" {
  source = "../../modules/Gcp/GKE"

  project_id = "my-project"
  region     = "us-central1"
  cluster_name = "my-cluster"
  
  # Network configuration
  network    = "projects/my-project/global/networks/my-vpc"
  subnetwork = "projects/my-project/regions/us-central1/subnetworks/my-subnet"
  
  # IP allocation policy
  ip_allocation_policy = {
    cluster_secondary_range_name  = "gke-pods-range"
    services_secondary_range_name = "gke-services-range"
    use_ip_aliases               = true
  }
  
  # Common labels
  common_labels = {
    environment = "dev"
    team        = "platform"
  }
  
  # Node pools
  node_pools = {
    "default-pool" = {
      name               = "default-pool"
      initial_node_count = 1
      machine_type       = "e2-medium"
      disk_size_gb       = 20
      disk_type          = "pd-standard"
      image_type         = "COS_CONTAINERD"
      preemptible        = false
      local_ssd_count    = 0
      service_account    = "gke-node-sa@my-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
      oauth_scopes       = ["https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `project_id` | The GCP project ID | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `region` | The GCP region | `string` | `"us-central1"` | no |
| `cluster_name` | The name of the GKE cluster | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `network` | The VPC network for the cluster | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `subnetwork` | The subnetwork for the cluster | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `enable_private_nodes` | Whether to enable private nodes | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `enable_private_endpoint` | Whether to enable private endpoint | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `release_channel` | The release channel for the cluster | `string` | `"REGULAR"` | no |
| `node_pools` | Map of node pools to create | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `service_accounts` | Map of service accounts to create | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `enable_monitoring` | Enable monitoring and alerting | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `enable_security_features` | Enable security features | `bool` | `true` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `cluster` | Information about the created GKE cluster |
| `node_pools` | Information about created node pools |
| `service_accounts` | Information about created service accounts |
| `cluster_name` | Name of the created cluster |
| `cluster_endpoint` | Endpoint of the created cluster |
| `connection_info` | Information for connecting to the cluster |
| `security_info` | Security configuration information |
| `performance_info` | Performance optimization information |


## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.0 |
| google | ~> 5.0 |

## Providers

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| google | ~> 5.0 |

